Merge pull request #29 from DGruenwald/posterize

Added Posterize

Added PutTexture

Draws an already existing texture onto another.
Also reimplemented mirrored repeat for gradients.
Fixed bad default for posterize step.

Added posterize filter

Posterize reduces the number of colors. Lower values for "step" results in fewer colors.

Merge pull request #26 from DGruenwald/master

Fixed repeat for gradients

Removed mirrored repeat

Decided to remove mirrored repeat because it sometimes flipped one pixel too early and returned the wrong color.

Fixed repeat for gradients

Also added mirrored repeat. However, it is buggy at the moment.

Conflicts:
	src/TexGen.js

Merge pull request #24 from DGruenwald/gradient-map

Gradient map

Added Normalize

Added the normalize filter, which maps the colors of the image to relative values between 0 and 1.
Especially useful for gradient maps.

Added GradientMap

Added the gradient map filter which assigns colors from a gradient based on the source value.
So, if the source pixel has a value of 0.2, it gets set to the color of the gradient at position 0.2.

Works best with grayscale "height maps."

As a side effect, color interpolators accept positions beyond 0 and 1 now.
toCanvas(): Allow passing a already created canvas.

Merge pull request #23 from DGruenwald/master

Added FractalNoise

Fixed check if argument exists.

Forgot to use typeof() here.

Added FractalNoise

Added a new type of noise: fractal noise, which is based on layers (or octaves) of noise being added on top of each other.
Also changed the RNG, yet again, to a hashing algorithm that generates numbers based on coordinates, which is required for fractal noise.
I've provided an example page for the noise as well.

Merge pull request #22 from DGruenwald/master

Make Noise seedable

Make resulting number absolute instead of the seed

I realized why a negative seed made just a black image. It was because the resulting random numbers were negative.

Replace xorshift with a linear congruential generator

Using "Math.abs(value)" when setting the seed since most negative numbers result in a black image.

Make Noise seedable

Changed Math.random() to the Xorshift random number algorithm and added ability to set the seed.
Code clean up and 3D preview improvements.
